article.headline: Lipscomb 87, Troy 79
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- James Poindexter scored 26 points and Lipscomb hit five free throws in the last 21 seconds to take an 87-79 victory Thursday night over Troy. Lipscomb (16-11, 11-9 Atlantic Sun) won its fourth straight game and broke a three-game winning streak by Troy (12-16, 10-9). Lipscomb made its five free throws after Troy edged to within three at 82-79 with 21 seconds left on three free throws by Bobby Dixon. Poindexter made two of them and finished 6-of-6 from the free-throw line. Lipscomb never trailed after Poindexter hit two free throws to make it 68-67 with just over five minutes left. Brian Fisk scored 19 points for Lipscomb and Eddie Ard had 10. Troy was led by Eddie Baker with 25 points, Corey Hornsby with 23 and Dixon with 18. Lipscomb was 29-of-37 from the free throw line to 11-of-15 for the Trojans.
